President Cyril Ramaphosa has been alerted to a second Covid-19 emergency if there was no swift action in reforming a patent “monopoly” system currently hampering the country’s access to tools needed to respond effectively to pandemics. Fix the Patent Laws (FTPL), a coalition of 40 patient advocacy groups and civil society organisations, has lamented that access to medicines and other health products in South Africa was hampered by a patent system that allowed for the granting of an excessive number of unwarranted patent monopolies. This results in exorbitant and arbitrary pricing by multinational pharmaceutical companies out for a profit at...